            <ins><h3><img src="https://www.ibiblio.org/pub/linux/docs/LuCaS/Presentaciones/200102linuxcol/filosofia/filosofia/images/tuxcola.gif" style="width:42px;height:42px;">Task 2: Installation of VS Code IDE software and extensions </h3></ins><br>
            <strong>Step 1: </strong></b> Install VS Code IDE for Windows (Host OS).<br>
            <br>
            <img src="https://github.com/WasinPipe/Assignment-07-12-2024/blob/main/Task%202%20step%201.png?raw=true"style="width: 400px;; height: 250px;"><br>
            <p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;">&rarr; In this step, installed VS Code IDE from <a href="https://code.visualstudio.com/">https://code.visualstudio.com/</a></p><br>
            <strong>Step 2: </strong>Install the Remote Development Extension Pack for VS Code IDE.</b> <br>
            <br>
            <img src="https://github.com/WasinPipe/Assignment-07-12-2024/blob/main/Task%202%20step%202.png?raw=true"style="width: 400px;; height: 250px;"><br>
            <p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;">&rarr; In this step, installed Remote-SSH by press ctrl + shift + x <br>
            to open extention and then search for Remote-SSH to install it</p><br>
            <strong>Step 3: </strong> Connect VS Code to the remote machine (Ubuntu).</b> <br>
            <br>
            <img src="https://github.com/WasinPipe/Assignment-07-12-2024/blob/main/Task%202%20step%203.1.png?raw=true"style="width: 500px;"><br>
            <p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;">&rarr; In this step, press ctrl + shift + p to open the command palette <br>
                and then type "Remote-SSH: Connect to Host..." and select it</p><br>
            <img src="https://github.com/WasinPipe/Assignment-07-12-2024/blob/main/Task%202%20step%203.2.png?raw=true"style="width: 500px;"><br>
            <p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;">&rarr; Enter the SSH connection string for Ubuntu machine so for this step,<br>
                I founded a problem about Ubuntu Desktop 's IP address,<br>
                I can't connect at first time</p><br>
            <img src="https://github.com/WasinPipe/Assignment-07-12-2024/blob/main/Task%202%20step%203.3.png?raw=true"style="width: 400px;; height: 250px;"><br>
            <p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;">&rarr; VS Code will open a new window connected to Ubuntu machine</p><br>
            <strong>Step 4: </strong>Install the PlatformIO extension for Remote Development.</b> <br>
            <br>
            <img src="https://github.com/WasinPipe/Assignment-07-12-2024/blob/main/Task%202%20step%204.png?raw=true"style="width: 400px;; height: 250px;"><br>
            <p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;">&rarr; In this step, installed PlatformIO by press ctrl + shift + x to open extention <br>
                and then search for PlatformIO to install it</p><br>
            <strong>Step 5: </strong></b>Create a project using PlatformIO and the Arduino framework. <br>
            <br>
            <img src="https://github.com/WasinPipe/Assignment-07-12-2024/blob/main/Task%202%20step%205.1.png?raw=true"style="width: 400px;; height: 250px;"><br>
            <p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;">&rarr; In this step, Click on the PlatformIO icon in the sidebar to open PlatformIO Home<br>
            So for this step, I have two problem about open PlatformIO Home <br>
            because it doesn't load the page and doesn't read python interpreter at first time</p><br>
            <img src="https://github.com/WasinPipe/Assignment-07-12-2024/blob/main/Task%202%20step%205.2.png?raw=true"style="width: 400px;; height: 250px;"><br>
            <p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;">&rarr; Create a new project in PlatformIO by Set your name for project,<br>
                Select board from list, nsure "Arduino" is selected as the framework and then<br>
                click "Finish" </p><br>
            <strong>Step 6: </strong></b>Build the Arduino sketch and upload it to the target.<br>
            <br>
            <img src="https://github.com/WasinPipe/Assignment-07-12-2024/blob/main/Task%202%20step%206.1.png?raw=true"style="width: 400px;; height: 250px;"><br>
            <p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;">&rarr; In this step, Open the src/main.cpp file in project file and then<br>
            write the Arduino code in this file</p><br>
            <img src="https://github.com/WasinPipe/Assignment-07-12-2024/blob/main/Task%202%20step6.2.png?raw=true"style="width: 400px;; height: 250px;"><br>
            <p style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;">&rarr; Click the &#10004; icon in the PlatformIO toolbar to build project and then<br>
            click the &rarr; icon in the PlatformIO toolbar to upload the sketch <br>
            to the Arduino board and Done!!!!!!</p><br>
